  "abstract": "The Federal Open Market Committee (\"Committee\") is finalizing its interim final rule amending the Committee's regulations under the Freedom of Information Act (\"FOIA\"). The FOIA Improvement Act of 2016 (\"Improvement Act\") amended the FOIA and required each federal agency to review its FOIA regulations and to issue certain revisions by December 27, 2016. Substantive revisions to the Committee's Rules Regarding Availability of Information (\"Rules\") were made to conform to the Improvement Act, and ",
